OPTIONS(description="This BigQuery table stores FHIR data related to healthcare encounters, which are interactions between a patient and healthcare provider(s) for the purpose of providing healthcare services or assessing the health status of a patient. Each record in the table represents a single encounter and includes key attributes such as encounter ID, patient ID, encounter type, status, class, start and end dates, service provider, and location. The table is designed to facilitate the analysis and reporting of healthcare encounters, supporting interoperability and data exchange in healthcare systems. It adheres to the FHIR standard, ensuring compatibility with other FHIR-compliant systems and applications. The data can be used for various purposes, including clinical research, healthcare analytics, and operational reporting. The table is optimized for performance and scalability, allowing for efficient querying and analysis of large volumes of encounter data.");